<exercise id="fs-id1167831882604">
<problem id="fs-id1167831882606">
<para id="fs-id1167835340804">Subtract: <span class="token">ⓐ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> <span class="token">ⓑ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−6</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>−4</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> <span class="token">ⓒ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−6</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> <span class="token">ⓓ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>−4</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1167834183611">
<para id="fs-id1167834539501"><span class="token">ⓐ</span> 2 <span class="token">ⓑ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> <span class="token">ⓒ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−10</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> <span class="token">ⓓ</span> 10</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
</note>
<note id="fs-id1167831882121" class="try">
<exercise id="fs-id1167835346029">
<problem id="fs-id1167835346032">
<para id="fs-id1167835346034">Subtract: <span class="token">ⓐ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>7</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> <span class="token">ⓑ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−7</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>−4</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> <span class="token">ⓒ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−7</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> <span class="token">ⓓ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>7</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>−4</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1167835367941">
<para id="fs-id1167835367944"><span class="token">ⓐ</span> 3 <span class="token">ⓑ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−3</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> <span class="token">ⓒ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−11</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> <span class="token">ⓓ</span> 11</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
</note>
<para id="fs-id1167834464452">Have you noticed that <emphasis effect="italics">subtraction of signed numbers can be done by adding the opposite</emphasis>? In the last example, <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−3</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> is the same as <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>−3</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>−1</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> and <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>−1</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> is the same as <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> You will often see this idea, the Subtraction Property, written as follows:</para>
<note id="fs-id1167835322024">
<title>Subtraction Property</title>
<equation id="fs-id1167835322029" class="unnumbered"><label/><m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mtext>−</m:mtext><m:mi>b</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></equation>
<para id="fs-id1167835281540">Subtracting a number is the same as adding its opposite.</para>
</note>

<example id="fs-id1167834539392">
